    <copyright>Copyright (c) marlocarlo</copyright>
    <summary>htop for Windows — beautiful, fast TUI system monitor</summary>
    <description>pstop is a full drop-in replacement for htop on Windows. Beautiful TUI system monitor with per-core CPU bars, memory/swap/network monitoring, tree view, process management, search/filter, 7 color schemes, and full mouse support. Installs both `pstop` and `htop` commands.

## Features
- Per-core CPU bars with user/kernel split
- Memory, Swap, Network and GPU header bars
- Tree view with collapsible nodes
- Search (F3) and Filter (F4)
- 4 tab views: Main, I/O, Net, GPU
- 7 color schemes
- Full mouse support
- ~1 MB binary, zero dependencies
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/marlocarlo/pstop/releases</releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <file src="tools\**" target="tools" />
  </files>
